[2] New South Wales (Dungog, Clarence)
Date: Wed 6 Jun 2018 7:00 AM AEST
Source: Dungog Chronicle [edited]
https://www.dungogchronicle.com.au/story/5443209/whooping-cough-cases/


Several cases of whooping cough have been confirmed in children from the Dungog and Clarence Town areas.

Dr Kat Taylor, a Hunter New England Health physician said while the local outbreak was not particularly unusual, it was a reminder for people to keep vigilant as the contagious bacterial disease can have severe implications. The disease, also known as pertussis, can be life threatening for babies.

"Whooping cough has been on the rise generally in NSW [New South Wales] for the past 10 years," she said. "There is always whooping cough about in the community and at times there is a bit more than others.

"The year [2018] to date [6 Jun 2018] figures for the Lower Hunter area show there have been 59 cases notified which is slightly up, with 18 more cases than this time last year [2017]." Whooping cough is a notifiable condition which means general practitioners, schools and day care centres must notify the public health unit when a case is diagnosed. "It's a reminder to check your vaccination status particularly if you are working with children and keep coughing children away from school or daycare," said Dr Taylor.

[byline: Michelle Mexon]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Dungog and Clarence are country towns, with populations of about 2100 residents each, in Dungog Shire, the Hunter region of New South Wales, Australia, about 215 km (134 mi) north of Sydney (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungog,_New_South_Wales and https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clarence_Town,_New_South_Wales). Dungog can be located on a map at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Dungog+NSW+2420,+Australia. The Hunter region, also commonly known as the Hunter Valley, is one of the largest river valleys on the NSW coast, and is most commonly known for its wineries and coal industry (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hunter_Region). - Mod.ML]

