[Lane county, with a population of 351 715 residents in 2010, is located on the Pacific coast in the US state of Oregon; its county seat is the city of Eugene, with a population of 156 185 residents, (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lane_County,_Oregon). Springfield is a smaller city, with a population of 59 403 residents, within the Eugene-Springfield Metropolitan Statistical Area (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springfield,_Oregon). A map showing the location of Lane county can be located at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Lane+County,+OR,+USA. - Mod.ML]

