Canada
---
[5] Ontario (Parry Sound district)
Date: Thu 5 Jul 2018, 7:00 AM ET
Source: CBC News [edited]
https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/sudbury/whooping-cough-powassan-health-unit-vaccination-1.4734371


Confirmed cases of whooping cough have been identified in Powassan and surrounding area. The North Bay Parry Sound District Health Unit says it has confirmed a few cases of pertussis -- commonly called whooping cough -- in the Powassan area.

Dr Jim Chirico, medical officer of health, is urging parents and guardians to check that their children have been vaccinated. Whooping cough vaccine's immunity drops substantially over time. If they haven't, he says, contact the health unit or a doctor.

