[The Dominican Republic, with a population of about 10 million residents, occupies the eastern 2 thirds of the island of Hispaniola, in the Greater Antilles archipelago in the Caribbean region; the western third of Hispaniola is occupied by the country of Haiti (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominican_Republic). San Cristóbal, a city and province, is located near the southern coast on the Caribbean Sea; the city is about 30 km (19 mi) west of the nation's capital, Santo Domingo (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Cristóbal,_Dominican_Republic). La Romana is a city and province on the southern coast on the Caribbean Sea, about 125 km (78 mi) east of Santo Domingo (https://www.google.com/maps/dir/La+Romana,+Dominican+Republic/Santo+Domingo,+Dominican+Republic). The city of Santiago, in the north central region of the country, is the 2nd-largest city in the Dominican Republic and the 4th-largest city in the Caribbean (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santiago_de_los_Caballeros). Santo Domingo Norte is a city immediately north of Santo Domingo (https://www.google.com/maps/place/Santo+Domingo+Norte,+Dominican+Republic). - Mod.ML

